enumsBuildType.description:
Enum indicating build type i.e. local, cluster vs GCB
- UNKNOWN_BUILD_TYPE: Could not determine Build Type
 - CLUSTER: Cluster Build
 - GCB: GCB Build
 - LOCAL: Local Build

enumsBuilderType.description:
Enum indicating builders used
- UNKNOWN_BUILDER_TYPE: Could not determine builder type
 - JIB: JIB Builder
 - BAZEL: Bazel Builder
 - BUILDPACKS: Buildpacks Builder
 - CUSTOM: Custom Builder
 - KANIKO: Kaniko Builder
 - DOCKER: Docker Builder
 - KO: Ko Builder

enumsClusterType.description:
Enum indicating cluster type the application is deployed to
- UNKNOWN_CLUSTER_TYPE: Could not determine Cluster Type
 - MINIKUBE: Minikube Cluster
 - GKE: GKE cluster
 - OTHER: All Cluster except Minikube and GKE

enumsDeployerType.description:
Enum indicating deploy tools used
- UNKNOWN_DEPLOYER_TYPE: Could not determine Deployer Type
 - HELM: Helm Deployer
 - KUSTOMIZE: Kustomize Deployer
 - KUBECTL: Kubectl Deployer
 - KPT: kpt Deployer

enumsLogLevel.description:
Enum indicating the log level of a line of output
- DEBUG: Debug Level
 - INFO: Info Level
 - WARN: Warn Level
 - ERROR: Error Level
 - FATAL: Fatal Level
 - PANIC: Panic Level
 - TRACE: Trace Level
 - STANDARD: User-visible output level

enumsRenderType.description:
Enum indicating render manifests type
- UNKNOWN_RENDER_TYPE: Could not determine Render Type
 - RAWK8S: Raw Manifests
 - KUSTOMIZE_MANIFEST: kustomize manifests
 - HELM_CHART: helm charts
 - KPT_MANIFEST: kpt manifests

enumsStatusCode.description:
Enum for Status codes
These error codes are prepended by Phase Name e.g. INIT, BUILD, TEST, DEPLOY, STATUSCHECK, DEVINIT
For Success Error codes, use range 200 to 250.
For Unknown error codes, use range 500 to 600.
For Cancelled Error code, use range 800 to 850.
- OK: A default status code for events that do not have an associated phase. Typically seen with the DevEndEvent event on success. - STATUSCHECK_SUCCESS: Status Check Success - BUILD_SUCCESS: Build Success - RENDER_SUCCESS: Render Success - DEPLOY_SUCCESS: Deploy Success - TEST_SUCCESS: Test Success - BUILD_PUSH_ACCESS_DENIED: Build error due to push access denied - BUILD_PROJECT_NOT_FOUND: Build error due to GCP project not found. - BUILD_DOCKER_DAEMON_NOT_RUNNING: Docker build error due to docker daemon not running - BUILD_USER_ERROR: Build error due to user application code, e.g. compilation error, dockerfile error etc - BUILD_DOCKER_UNAVAILABLE: Build error due to docker not available - BUILD_DOCKER_UNAUTHORIZED: Docker build error due to user not authorized to perform the action - BUILD_DOCKER_SYSTEM_ERR: Docker system build error - BUILD_DOCKER_NOT_MODIFIED_ERR: Docker build error due to Docker build container is already in the desired state - BUILD_DOCKER_NOT_IMPLEMENTED_ERR: Docker build error indicating a feature not supported - BUILD_DOCKER_DATA_LOSS_ERR: Docker build error indicates that for given build, data was lost or there is data corruption - BUILD_DOCKER_FORBIDDEN_ERR: Docker build error indicates user is forbidden to perform the build or step/action. - BUILD_DOCKER_CONFLICT_ERR: Docker build error due to some internal error and docker container state conflicts with the requested action and can't be performed - BUILD_DOCKER_ERROR_NOT_FOUND: Docker build error indicates the requested object does not exist - BUILD_DOCKER_INVALID_PARAM_ERR: Docker build error indication invalid parameter sent to docker command - BUILD_DOCKERFILE_NOT_FOUND: Docker build failed due to dockerfile not found - BUILD_DOCKER_CACHE_FROM_PULL_ERR: Docker build failed due `cacheFrom` user config error - BUILD_DOCKER_GET_DIGEST_ERR: Build error due to digest for built artifact could not be retrieved from docker daemon. - BUILD_DOCKER_NO_SPACE_ERR: Build error due no space left in docker. - BUILD_REGISTRY_GET_DIGEST_ERR: Build error due to digest for built artifact could not be retrieved from registry. - BUILD_UNKNOWN_JIB_PLUGIN_TYPE: Build error indicating unknown Jib plugin type. Should be one of [maven, gradle] - BUILD_JIB_GRADLE_DEP_ERR: Build error determining dependency for jib gradle project. - BUILD_JIB_MAVEN_DEP_ERR: Build error determining dependency for jib gradle project. - INIT_DOCKER_NETWORK_LISTING_CONTAINERS: Docker build error when listing containers. - INIT_DOCKER_NETWORK_INVALID_CONTAINER_NAME: Docker build error indicating an invalid container name (or id). - INIT_DOCKER_NETWORK_CONTAINER_DOES_NOT_EXIST: Docker build error indicating the container referenced does not exists in the docker context used. - INIT_DOCKER_NETWORK_INVALID_MODE: Docker Network invalid mode - INIT_DOCKER_NETWORK_PARSE_ERR: Error parsing Docker Network mode - BUILD_GCB_CREATE_BUILD_ERR: GCB Create Build Error - BUILD_GCB_GET_BUILD_ID_ERR: GCB error indicating an error to fetch build id. - BUILD_GCB_GET_BUILD_STATUS_ERR: GCB error indicating an error to fetch build status. - BUILD_GCB_GET_BUILD_LOG_ERR: GCB error indicating an error to fetch build logs. - BUILD_GCB_COPY_BUILD_LOG_ERR: GCB error indicating an error to fetch build status. - BUILD_GCB_GET_BUILT_IMAGE_ERR: GCB error indicating an error retrieving the built image id. - BUILD_GCB_BUILD_FAILED: GCB error indicating build failure. - BUILD_GCB_BUILD_INTERNAL_ERR: GCB error indicating build failure due to internal errror. - BUILD_GCB_BUILD_TIMEOUT: GCB error indicating build failure due to timeout. - BUILD_GCB_GENERATE_BUILD_DESCRIPTOR_ERR: GCB error to generate the build descriptor. - BUILD_GCB_UPLOAD_TO_GCS_ERR: GCB error to upload to GCS. - BUILD_GCB_JIB_DEPENDENCY_ERR: GCB error to fetch jib artifact dependency. - BUILD_GCB_GET_DEPENDENCY_ERR: GCB error to fetch artifact dependency. - BUILD_GCB_GET_GCS_BUCKET_ERR: GCB error to get GCS bucket. - BUILD_GCB_CREATE_BUCKET_ERR: GCB error to create a GCS bucket. - BUILD_GCB_EXTRACT_PROJECT_ID: GCB error to extract Project ID. - BUILD_GET_CLOUD_STORAGE_CLIENT_ERR: GCB error to get cloud storage client to perform GCS operation. - BUILD_GET_CLOUD_BUILD_CLIENT_ERR: GCB error to get cloud build client to perform GCB operations. - BUILD_UNKNOWN_PLATFORM_FLAG: Value provided to --platform flag cannot be parsed - BUILD_CROSS_PLATFORM_ERR: Cross-platform build failures - BUILD_CROSS_PLATFORM_NO_REGISTRY_ERR: Multi-platfor build fails due to no container registry set - STATUSCHECK_IMAGE_PULL_ERR: Container image pull error - STATUSCHECK_CONTAINER_CREATING: Container creating error - STATUSCHECK_RUN_CONTAINER_ERR: Container run error - STATUSCHECK_CONTAINER_TERMINATED: Container is already terminated - STATUSCHECK_DEPLOYMENT_ROLLOUT_PENDING: Deployment waiting for rollout - STATUSCHECK_STANDALONE_PODS_PENDING: Standalone pods pending to stabilize - enumsSuggestionCode.description:
Enum for Suggestion codes
- NIL: default nil suggestion.
This is usually set when no error happens.
 - ADD_DEFAULT_REPO: Add Default Repo
 - CHECK_DEFAULT_REPO: Verify Default Repo
 - CHECK_DEFAULT_REPO_GLOBAL_CONFIG: Verify default repo in the global config
 - GCLOUD_DOCKER_AUTH_CONFIGURE: run gcloud docker auth configure
 - DOCKER_AUTH_CONFIGURE: Run docker auth configure
 - CHECK_GCLOUD_PROJECT: Verify Gcloud Project
 - CHECK_DOCKER_RUNNING: Check if docker is running
 - FIX_USER_BUILD_ERR: Fix User Build Error
 - DOCKER_BUILD_RETRY: Docker build internal error, try again
 - FIX_CACHE_FROM_ARTIFACT_CONFIG: Fix `cacheFrom` config for given artifact and try again
 - FIX_SKAFFOLD_CONFIG_DOCKERFILE: Fix `dockerfile` config for a given artifact and try again.
 - FIX_JIB_PLUGIN_CONFIGURATION: Use a supported Jib plugin type
 - FIX_DOCKER_NETWORK_CONTAINER_NAME: Docker build network invalid docker container name (or id).
 - CHECK_DOCKER_NETWORK_CONTAINER_RUNNING: Docker build network container not existing in the current context.
 - FIX_DOCKER_NETWORK_MODE_WHEN_EXTRACTING_CONTAINER_NAME: Executing extractContainerNameFromNetworkMode with a non valid mode (only
container mode allowed)
 - RUN_DOCKER_PRUNE: Prune Docker image
 - SET_CLEANUP_FLAG: Set Cleanup flag for skaffold command.
 - BUILD_FIX_UNKNOWN_PLATFORM_FLAG: Check value provided to the `--platform` flag
 - BUILD_INSTALL_PLATFORM_EMULATORS: Check if QEMU platform emulators are installed
 - SET_PUSH_AND_CONTAINER_REGISTRY: Set --push and container registry to run a multi-platform build
 - CHECK_CLUSTER_CONNECTION: Check cluster connection
 - CHECK_MINIKUBE_STATUS: Check minikube status
 - INSTALL_HELM: Install helm tool
 - UPGRADE_HELM: Upgrade helm tool
 - FIX_SKAFFOLD_CONFIG_HELM_ARTIFACT_OVERRIDES: Fix helm `releases.artifactOverrides` config to match with
`build.artifacts` (no longer used in Skaffold v2)
 - UPGRADE_HELM32: Upgrade helm version to v3.2.0 and higher.
 - FIX_SKAFFOLD_CONFIG_HELM_CREATE_NAMESPACE: Set `releases.createNamespace` to false.
 - INVALID_KPT_MANIFESTS: check the Kptfile validation.
 - ALIGN_KPT_INVENTORY: align the inventory info in kpt live apply.
 - INSTALL_KUBECTL: Install kubectl tool
 - SPECIFY_CLOUD_RUN_LOCATION: Specify Cloud Run Location
 - CHECK_CONTAINER_LOGS: Container run error
 - CHECK_READINESS_PROBE: Pod Health check error
 - CHECK_CONTAINER_IMAGE: Check Container image
 - ADDRESS_NODE_MEMORY_PRESSURE: Node pressure error
 - ADDRESS_NODE_DISK_PRESSURE: Node disk pressure error
 - ADDRESS_NODE_NETWORK_UNAVAILABLE: Node network unavailable error
 - ADDRESS_NODE_PID_PRESSURE: Node PID pressure error
 - ADDRESS_NODE_UNSCHEDULABLE: Node unschedulable error
 - ADDRESS_NODE_UNREACHABLE: Node unreachable error
 - ADDRESS_NODE_NOT_READY: Node not ready error
 - ADDRESS_FAILED_SCHEDULING: Scheduler failure error
 - CHECK_HOST_CONNECTION: Cluster Connectivity error
 - START_MINIKUBE: Minikube is stopped: use `minikube start`
 - UNPAUSE_MINIKUBE: Minikube is paused: use `minikube unpause`
 - RUN_DOCKER_PULL: Run Docker pull for the image with v1 manifest and try again.
 - SET_RENDER_FLAG_OFFLINE_FALSE: Rerun with correct offline flag value.
 - KPTFILE_MANUAL_INIT: Manually run `kpt pkg init` or `kpt live init`
 - KPTFILE_CHECK_YAML: Check if the Kptfile is correct.
 - REMOVE_NAMESPACE_FROM_MANIFESTS: Remove namespace from manifests
 - CONFIG_CHECK_FILE_PATH: Check configuration file path
 - CONFIG_CHECK_DEPENDENCY_DEFINITION: Check dependency config definition
 - CONFIG_CHANGE_NAMES: Change config name to avoid duplicates
 - CONFIG_CHECK_FILTER: Check config filter
 - CONFIG_CHECK_PROFILE_DEFINITION: Check profile definition in current config
 - CONFIG_CHECK_DEPENDENCY_PROFILES_SELECTION: Check active profile selection for dependency config
 - CONFIG_CHECK_PROFILE_SELECTION: Check profile selection flag
 - CONFIG_FIX_API_VERSION: Fix config API version or upgrade the skaffold binary
 - CONFIG_ALLOWLIST_VALIDATORS: Only the allow listed validators are acceptable in skaffold-managed mode.
 - CONFIG_ALLOWLIST_transformers: Only the allow listed transformers are acceptable in skaffold-managed
mode.
 - CONFIG_FIX_MISSING_MANIFEST_FILE: Check mising manifest file section of config and fix as needed.
 - CONFIG_ENABLE_REMOTE_REPO_SYNC: Enable remote repo sync, or clone manually
 - CONFIG_FIX_SKAFFOLD_CONFIG_VERSION: Upgrade skaffold config version to latest
 - INSPECT_USE_MODIFY_OR_NEW_PROFILE: Create new build env in a profile instead, or use the 'modify' command
 - INSPECT_USE_ADD_BUILD_ENV: Check profile selection, or use the 'add' command instead
 - INSPECT_CHECK_INPUT_PROFILE: Check profile flag value
 - OPEN_ISSUE: Open an issue so this situation can be diagnosed
 - CHECK_CUSTOM_COMMAND: Test error suggestion codes

enumsTesterType.description:
Enum indicating test tools used
- UNKNOWN_TEST_TYPE: Could not determine Test Type
 - UNIT: Unit tests
 - CONTAINER_STRUCTURE_TEST: Container Structure tests

v2ActionableErr.description: `ActionableErr` defines an error that occurred along with an optional list of suggestions

v2ApplicationLogEvent.description: `ApplicationLogEvent` represents a log that comes from one of the pods running in the user's application.

additional.description: Additional key value pairs to describe the build pipeline

artifacts.description:
A map of `artifact name -> build-state`. Artifact name is defined in the `skaffold.yaml`. The `build-state` can be:
- `"NotStarted"`: not yet started
- `"InProgress"`: build started
- `"Complete"`: build succeeded
- `"Failed"`: build failed

v2BuildState.description: `BuildState` maps Skaffold artifacts to their current build states

v2BuildSubtaskEvent.description:
`BuildSubtaskvent` describes the build status per artifact, and will be emitted by Skaffold anytime a build starts or finishes, successfully or not.
If the build fails, an error will be attached to the event.

v2CloudRunReadyEvent.description:
A Resource StatusCheck Event for a Cloud Run Service.
Indicates that a Cloud Run Service has deployed successfully and is serving
on the specified URL

v2DebuggingContainerEvent.description: DebuggingContainerEvent is raised when a debugging container is started or terminated

v2DeployState.description: `DeployState` describes the status of the current deploy

v2DeploySubtaskEvent.description:
`DeploySubtaskEvent` represents the status of a deployment, and is emitted by Skaffold
anytime a deployment starts or completes, successfully or not.

v2Event.description:
`Event` describes an event in the Skaffold process.
It is one of MetaEvent, BuildEvent, TestEvent, DeployEvent, PortEvent, StatusCheckEvent, ResourceStatusCheckEvent, FileSyncEvent, or DebuggingContainerEvent.

v2ExecState.description: `ExecState` describes the state of the current exec

v2ExecSubtaskEvent.description:
`ExecSubtaskEvent` represents the status of an exec, and is emitted by Skaffold
anytime an exec starts or completes, successfully or not.

v2FileSyncState.description: `FileSyncState` contains the status of the current file sync

v2IntOrString.description: IntOrString is a type that can hold an int32 or a string.

v2Intent.description: Intent represents user intents for a given phase.

additional.description: Additional key value pairs to describe the build pipeline

v2PortForwardEvent.description: PortForwardEvent Event describes each port forwarding event.

v2RenderState.description: `RenderState` describes the current state of the render

v2RenderSubtaskEvent.description:
`RenderSubtaskEvent` represents the status of a render, and is emitted by Skaffold
anytime a render starts or completes, successfully or not.

level.description: string origin = 3; // REMOVED: which tool the output came from ex: skaffold, docker

v2SkaffoldLogEvent.description: `SkaffoldLogEvent` represents a piece of output that comes from a skaffold run, for example: "Generating tags...", "Step 1/3 : FROM gcr.io/distroless/base"

v2State.description: `State` represents the current state of the Skaffold components

resources.description:
A map of `resource name -> status-check-state`. Where `resource-name` is the kubernetes resource name. The `status-check-state` can be
- `"NotStarted"`: indicates that `status-check` has just started.
- `"InProgress"`: InProgress is sent after every resource check is complete.
- `"Succeeded"`: - `"Failed"`:

v2StatusCheckState.description: `StatusCheckState` describes the state of status check of current deployed resources.

v2StatusCheckSubtaskEvent.description:
A Resource StatusCheck Event, indicates progress for each kubernetes deployment.
For every resource, there will be exactly one event with `status` *Succeeded* or *Failed* event.
There can be multiple events with `status` *Pending*.
Skaffold polls for resource status every 0.5 second. If the resource status changes, an event with `status` Pending, Complete and Failed
will be sent with the new status.

v2Suggestion.description: Suggestion defines the action a user needs to recover from an error.

v2TaskEvent.description:
`TaskEvent` represent the different larger phases of a skaffold session, for example Build, Deploy, etc.
If a phase fails, an actionable error will be attached

v2TerminationEvent.description: `TerminationEvent` marks the end of the skaffold session

v2TestState.description: `TestState` describes the current state of the test

v2TestSubtaskEvent.description:
`TestSubtaskEvent` represents the status of a test, and is emitted by Skaffold
anytime a test starts or completes, successfully or not.

v2TriggerState.description: TriggerState represents trigger state for a given phase.

v2VerifyState.description: `VerifyState` describes the current state of the render

v2VerifySubtaskEvent.description:
`VerifyEvent` represents the status of a render, and is emitted by Skaffold
anytime a render starts or completes, successfully or not.
